\c 11  
\p
\v 1 Now a certain man was sick, Lazarus from Bethany, of the village of Mary and her sister, Martha. 
\v 2 It was that Mary who had anointed the Lord with ointment and wiped his feet with her hair, whose brother Lazarus was sick. 
\v 3 The sisters therefore sent to him, saying, “Lord, behold, he for whom you have great affection is sick.” 
\p
\v 4 But when Jesus heard it, he said, \wj “\+w This\+w* sickness \+w is\+w* \+w not\+w* \+w to\+w* \+w death\+w*, \+w but\+w* \+w for\+w* \+w the\+w* \+w glory\+w* \+w of\+w* \+w God\+w*, \+w that\+w* \+w God\+w*’s \+w Son\+w* \+w may\+w* \+w be\+w* \+w glorified\+w* \+w by\+w* \+w it\+w*.”\wj* 
\v 5 Now Jesus loved Martha, and her sister, and Lazarus. 
\v 6 When therefore he heard that he was sick, he stayed two days in the place where he was. 
\v 7 Then after this he said to the disciples, \wj “\+w Let\+w*’s \+w go\+w* \+w into\+w* \+w Judea\+w* \+w again\+w*.”\wj* 
\p
